<Title>The Local Government Finance (Wales) Act 2024 (Commencement No. 1) Order 2026</Title>
<MadeDate>
<Text>Made</Text>
<DateText>22 January 2026</DateText>
</MadeDate>
<SecondaryPreamble>
<EnactingText>
<Para>
<Text>The Welsh Ministers make the following Order in exercise of the powers conferred on them by section 23(5) of the Local Government Finance (Wales) Act 2024<FootnoteRef Ref="f00001"/>.</Text>
</Para>
</EnactingText>
</SecondaryPreamble>
</SecondaryPrelims>
<Body DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/wsi/2026/14/body/enacted" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/wsi/2026/14/body" NumberOfProvisions="2">
<P1group>
<Title>Title</Title>
<P1 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/wsi/2026/14/article/1/enacted" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/wsi/2026/14/article/1" id="article-1">
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text>The title of this Order is the Local Government Finance (Wales) Act 2024 (Commencement No. 1) Order 2026.</Text>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group>
<Title>Provision coming into force on 1 April 2026</Title>
<P1 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/wsi/2026/14/article/2/enacted" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/wsi/2026/14/article/2" id="article-2">
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text>Section 18 (discounts) of the Local Government Finance (Wales) Act 2024 comes into force on 1 April 2026, in so far as the section is not already in force.</Text>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
